sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Scheduler<br/>(in-process goroutine)
    participant Cache as In-Memory Cache
    participant RemoteK8s as Remote Kueue Cluster<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,Cache: Flow 1: Job Admission (Standard Path)

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f pytorchjob.yaml<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / Client Cert
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate (admission review)<br/>mTLS (API server cert)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Apply defaults: queue-name label,<br/>suspend=true, managed-by annotation
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated admission response
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate (admission review)<br/>mTLS (API server cert)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate queue-name, TAS annotations,<br/>immutability constraints
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated admission response
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job created (suspended)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch event: new PyTorchJob<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Bearer Token
    Controller->>Controller: Create Workload CR from job spec<br/>(pod sets, resource requirements)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workload CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Bearer Token

    Scheduler->>Cache: Read ClusterQueue state<br/>(quotas, flavors, utilization)
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Evaluate admission:<br/>quota check, priority, fair sharing,<br/>flavor assignment, preemption
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Update Workload.status.admission<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Bearer Token

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Resume job (set suspend=false)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job pods created and scheduled

    Note over Controller,RemoteK8s: Flow 2: MultiKueue Workload Distribution

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch admitted Workload<br/>with MultiKueue AdmissionCheck
    Controller->>RemoteK8s: Create remote Workload + Job<br/>Auth: kubeconfig from Secret
    RemoteK8s-->>Controller: Remote Workload status updates<br/>Auth: kubeconfig watch
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Sync remote status to local Workload<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Bearer Token

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Provisioning Request (Autoscaler Integration)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Workload needs unavailable resources
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ProvisioningRequest CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Bearer Token
    Note right of K8sAPI: Cluster Autoscaler processes<br/>ProvisioningRequest, provisions nodes
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: ProvisioningRequest status: Provisioned
    Controller->>Scheduler: Re-evaluate admission with new capacity
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Admit Workload
